&quot;Oh no!&quot; I told Blake, and ran off, trying to find Mr. Potato. Unfortunately, there were a lot of places for him to run off to. I checked all over... And couldn't find Mr. Potato! Discouraged, I stopped and tried to think of where he might have run off to. Clearly he was lost, or he probably would have returned already...<br />
<br />
As I thought, Kim was giving a behind-the-scenes tour in the lab next door. &quot;This is our octopus feeding log&quot; I heard her say, &quot;octopi are estimated to be about as smart as a three-to-five year old human child... right now we're even teaching ours to disassemble and reassemble a Mr. Potato Head!&quot; Suddenly it hit me. What if...? Oh no! I checked the schedule, and asked Jane if she had seen Christophe. <br />
<br />
&quot;I think he's gone to feed the octopus,&quot; Jane replied.<br />
<br />
Hoping that I was being paranoid, I ran towards the octopus tank. Mr. Potato had been missing for an awfully long time...<br />
<br />
To my horror, my suspicions were correct. Christophe had already dropped Mr. Potato... my Mr. Potato... into the tank, and the octopus-in-training appeared to be attempting to eat his right eye. The training session wasn't a total failure, however, because she had done some reassembling... unfortunately, none of it was done correctly. &quot;Christophe!&quot; I said, &quot;that's my guest!&quot; And he quickly rescued Mr. Potato.<br />
<br />
Needless to say, Mr. Potato's trip was ruined. &quot;I want to go home!&quot; Cried his mouth from the place where his left leg should have been. Defeated, I reassembled him correctly and brought him back through the portal... ready to ship him off in hopes of a better trip.&quot;<br />
