<span style="font-weight:bold;">Sock Pie</span>:<br />
&quot;Day one did not go well...I had been very busy and didn't bother to check incoming. As it happened, I heard some peculiar noises coming from incoming. After searching for two hours in the sea of neglected boxes, I came upon a very angry Mr. Potatohead. He had waved his small white arms wildly and fired a string of curses at me. He accused me of attempting to murder him by starving him in a box.<br />
<br />
Mr. Potatohead grew agitated that with one violent wave of his arms, his ears snapped off. Mr. Potatohead howled in anger and looked for a scapegoat. Unfortunately, I was the nearest person at the time. &quot;YOU STOLE MY EARS,&quot; he shrieked. &quot;MY BEAUTIFUL PINK EARS, ALL GONE! GIVE 'EM BACK! GIVE 'EM BACK RIGHT NOW!&quot;<br />
<br />
Screaming had taken a lot of energy out of Mr. Potatohead. He abruptly went silent and collapsed on the floor, snoring.<br />
<br />
Meanwhile, his ears had rolled away, down the street. Knowing that many people wanted ears for their own Mr. Potatoheads, I raced after them. Luckily I snatched the ears before they attracted too much attention.<br />
<br />
<img src="http://img249.imageshack.us/img249/8411/earstm5.png"><br />
<br />
When I had returned to my house, I found Mr. Potatohead playing in my greenhouse with Cyra, my mischievous little imp. I called the little potato over and told him to hold still. He didn't, and squirmed quite a bit, but I still managed to pop the ears back in place. After that, I showed him into my trophy room. I expected him to be at least mildly impressed, but he just yawned in a bored sort of way and demanded me for some wine. I went to my storage room and offered him my best homemade redsberry wine. He gulped it down and held out his glass for more. Soon my whole supply of redsberry wine had been depleted. Seeing there was no more, Mr. Potatohead drunkenly settled in my bed for a nap.<br />
<br />
When night had arrived, Mr. Potatohead was still sleeping. Not wanting to squish my guest, I went to find a couch. Unfortunately, my pets had gotten to the couches before me.<br />
<br />
That night I had slept on the floor.<br />
<br />
I awoke to see Mr. Potatohead bashing me over and over again on my arm with a little yellow plastic shovel. I felt very irritated today, partly because of my now nonexistent wine supply, and partly because it was three in the morning. The bruises forming on my arm did not help.<br />
<br />
&quot;What is it?&quot; I groaned.<br />
<br />
&quot;There were zombies in your house,&quot; Mr. Potatohead said.<br />
<br />
&quot;Were?&quot;<br />
<br />
Mr. Potatohead nodded, smiling triumphantly. &quot;I ran over to the plaza and called for help, and lots of pets came, and they got rid of the ugly beasties.&quot;<br />
<br />
&quot;What?! You killed Ziggly and Clara? Wait a second...how did the mob get into the house?&quot;<br />
<br />
&quot;Oh, well they, um...got a bit...carried away...&quot;<br />
<br />
<img src="http://img247.imageshack.us/img247/944/zombieed0.png"><br />
<br />
Alarmed, I jumped out of my sleeping bag and ran out of the bedroom, heading to the living room. All my pets were huddled together, looking shaken. They all held weapons; sticks, swords, shovels, sculpting knives, etcetera.<br />
<br />
&quot;Okay, WHAT happened?&quot; I demanded, looking at the debris everywhere. The wallpaper had been torn down. Some of the roof had fallen off. Windows were shattered, and the door was gone. And there were pet-shaped holes in the wall.<br />
<br />
&quot;We tried to defend our home when the crazy mob attacked,&quot; Exotic explained, &quot;but there were too many. We were outnumbered&quot;<br />
<br />
&quot;I wish Psypets offered house insurance,&quot; I muttered. I pointed at the troublesome potato and told him to get back to bed.<br />
<br />
I told my pets to help me get the house back together. We worked long and accomplished little. Hours later, Mr. Potatohead emerged from the bedroom and asked for some wine. I rolled my eyes, but not wanting to disappoint a guest, headed to the marketplace. I came back, grocery bags filled with alcoholic beverages.<br />
<br />
The days went on like this: Mr. Potatohead wakes up, asks for wine and other snacks, and waits as I go to the marketplace. I buy food and wine, and come back. He drinks most of the wine, then takes a nap. He wakes up, plays hide-and-go-seek or something with Cyra (they had become close friends), and then drinks the rest of the wine and sleeps until the next morning.<br />
<br />
I watched my savings drop lower and lower. Even Lakisha asked me what I needed all the money for. &quot;You wouldn't believe me,&quot; was what I always replied. Who knew one little potato could devour so much food and drink?<br />
<br />
Finally I decided to do something about my diminishing cash. That morning I went to the market, as usual, but instead of redsberry and blueberry wine, I bought tea. All kinds of tea; sweet tea, berry tea, green tea, ginger tea, and even fire spice tea. I returned to my house (which by the way is looking a lot better now) and, carrying a large box of tea, went to find the hungry potato.<br />
<br />
Mr. Potatohead was in the kitchen, hunting for leftovers he may have missed. Upon seeing my return, he looked up in anticipation.<br />
<br />
&quot;Nope, it isn't wine this time,&quot; I said, ignoring his disappointed look. &quot;I got something new for you. Tea!&quot;<br />
<br />
Mr. Potatohead looked curiously at the cups of steaming tea I placed before him. He took a cautious sip. Then he smiled and drained the whole cup.<br />
<br />
&quot;This is very good,&quot; he declared, dumping sweet berry tea in his mouth. I grinned. Perhaps he had finally gotten over his obsession with wine.<br />
<br />
&quot;I know someone who's got more tea,&quot; I told him.<br />
<br />
&quot;Mmm? Whmph?&quot; the potato couldn't speak clearly, he was busy drinking a cup of fire spice tea.<br />
<br />
&quot;The Tea Queen!&quot; And with that, I grabbed his tiny arm and placed him, along with the box of tea, into my shiny new teleporter. After typing in Rika's name, I pushed the Make It So button, and sent him to Rika's house.&quot;<br />
